	"system": {
		"description": "<p>While you have become used to your limbs occasionally giving up on you, you know that your opponents probably do not have that practice.</p><p>As an attack action (it can replace 1 attack when you gain Extra Attack): choose a number of creatures up to your proficiency bonus that you can see within 30ft. Those creatures make Constitution save versus your maneuver DC or fall prone. You can use this ability a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus per long rest.</p><p>At level 6, when you deal poison damage to an enemy, your maneuver DC when using this ability increases by 1 against that enemy. At level 14, your maneuver DC for this ability increases by a total of 2 against an enemy you’ve hit with poison damage. Once an enemy fails their saving throw against this ability, you must deal poison damage again to increase your maneuver DC this way again against that enemy.</p>",
